Azure Defender for Cloud is a security management tool that provides threat protection and security recommendations for Azure resources.

It continuously monitors resources and identifies vulnerabilities.

For example, it may detect that a virtual machine is missing critical security updates and recommend fixes.

A real-life use case is a company monitoring its cloud infrastructure for threats. Defender for Cloud alerts administrators about suspicious activities.

Another example is compliance monitoring, where organizations ensure their resources meet security standards.

This service helps improve security posture and protect against cyber threats.
